More particularly, the Board analyzed, from para. 7 to 11 of the decision, the evidence and the testimony before it to determine if the applicant had a well-founded fear of persecution (s. 96 of the
Act
). From para. 12 to 15, the Board consequently did the same in order to determine if the applicant would face a risk of danger, torture or cruel treatment if she would return to Haiti (s. 97 of the
Act
).
